  "texts": [
    "These models were chosen as they are trained on biomedical language similar to that found on drug labels, and were demonstrated to perform well on a variety of relevant NLP tasks (37).",
    "We evaluated the performance of both models on the Demner-Fushman et al.",
    "annotated label set, with both a standard train/validation/test 80/10/10 split used to train the model, and the TAC 2017 evaluation script.",
    "The PubMedBERT-based model achieved a modest performance improvement over the ClinicalBERT-based model, and notably it performed more consistently across the two different evaluations.",
    "The detailed performance metrics for each model and evaluation set are detailed in (Supplementary Figure 4A)."
  ],
